Citation.sTitle: Heat capacities and enthalpies of fusion of lithium and rubidium nitrates. Heat capacities, enthalpies of fusion and enthalpies of formation of the intermediate compounds Ag0.5Rb0.5NO3 and Li0.5Rb0.5NO3.
Citation.sAbstract: Due to the numerous applications of the molten salt systems (chemical processes, metallurgical research, transfert of thermal energy produced from solar radiation ), the determination of the thermodynamical functions and the study of the phase diagrams of the binary and ternary systems of alkali nitrate are important for a better exploitation of this systems. So, the heat capacities as well as the enthalpies of fusion and solid state transitions of rubidium nitrate, lithium nitrate and of the intermediate compounds Ag0.5Rb0.5NO3 and Li0.5Rb0.5NO3, in solid and liquid states, have been measured by differential scanning calorimetry (DSC). The enthalpies of formation of Ag0.5Rb0.5NO3 and Li0.5Rb0.5NO3 at 298 K have been deduced.
Citation.sKeyword: Heat capacities, heat of formation, intermediate compound, lithium nitrate,
phase transition enthalpy, rubidium nitrate, silver nitrate.
